{
  "texts": [
    "The aim of the fusion is to be able to jointly look at the result of different modalities and take an informed decision in deciding what the result to report to patients is-if a diagnosis is normal, benign, or malignant.",
    "In Table 5, we show that all randomly selected samples of histology were malignant, and the prediction also correctly labeled them as malignant.",
    "Similarly, original labels for the mammography samples selected for the evaluation were originally normal with the prediction labeling them as normal.",
    "Furthermore, we explored the labeling of the remapping.",
    "Interestingly, we noticed that the remapping models used also showed a consistency in the cases of histology and mammography samples correspondingly to those of actual and predicted."
  ]
}